main event: Multiple witnesses, including USAF personnel, observed a cigar-shaped object that displayed technical intelligence over Redding, California on October 9, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed to be oscillating or vibrating and emitting pulsating sounds or a loud roar lasting for two seconds each time.
The object hovered at a low altitude, then rose to a high altitude and moved to the southeast of Redding.
The object was verified to be seen by multiple witnesses, including USAF personnel who were refueling aircraft.
The object was described as cigar-shaped, with one side appearing green and the other side orange/red/white.
The object remained in sight during the entire duration of the sighting, which lasted for approximately two hours.
sighted object: a cigar-shaped object with fluctuating colors
